value.value: Organogenesis stage during which the straightening of the trunk starts.

definition.value: Usually starts between day 48 and day 51 post-fertilization.

value.value: Organogenesis stage during which upper limbs are longer and bent at elbow.

definition.value: Usually starts between day 51 and day 53 post-fertilization, beginning of the eighth week.

value.value: Organogenesis stage during which hands and feet turned inward.

definition.value: Usually starts between day 53 and day 54 post-fertilization.

value.value: Organogenesis stage during which eyelids and external ears appear.

definition.value: Usually starts between day 54 and day 56 post-fertilization.

value.value: Organogenesis stage during which the head, the body, and the limbs are rounded structures.

definition.value: Usually starts between day 56 and day 60 post-fertilization.

value.value: Carnegie developmental stage 5 defined by a solid trophoblast.
Carnegie developmental stage 5 defined by a trophoblastic lacunae.
Carnegie developmental stage 5 defined by a lacunar vascular circle.
Carnegie developmental stage 6 during which chorionic villi appear.
Carnegie developmental stage 6 during which the primitive streak appears.
Prenatal stage that starts with the fully formed embryo and ends at birth.

definition.value: Prenatal development is a continuum, with no clear defining feature distinguishing an embryo from a fetus. The use of the term "fetus" generally implies that a mammalian embryo has developed to the point of being recognizable as belonging to its own species, though the point at which this occurs is subjective. [Wikipedia:Fetus]

value.value: Prenatal stage that starts with fertilization and ends at birth.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 8 and under 9 weeks of development.

definition.value: External genitalia begin to distinguish themselves as either male or female. Eyelids are completely closed, and vocal ligaments appear (see http://ehd.org/resources_bpd_documentation_english.php).

value.value: Fetal stage when the fetus is over 9 and under 10 weeks of development.

definition.value: The fingernails and toenails begin to develop and unique fingerprints appear. Ossification is underway in most bones (see http://ehd.org/resources_bpd_documentation_english.php).

value.value: Fetal stage when the fetus is over 10 and under 11 weeks of development.

definition.value: The nose and lips are completely formed, and external genitalia can be distinguished as male or female (see http://ehd.org/resources_bpd_documentation_english.php).

value.value: Fetal stage when the fetus is over 11 and under 12 weeks of development.

definition.value: Upper limb length has nearly reached its final proportion to body size (see http://ehd.org/resources_bpd_documentation_english.php). The assignation of this week to the fourth or third LMP month is debatable (see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Prenatal_development_table.svg).

value.value: Fetal stage when the fetus is over 12 and under 13 weeks of development.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 13 and under 14 weeks of development.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 14 and under 15 weeks of development.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 15 and under 16 weeks of development.

definition.value: The assignation of this week to the fifth or fourth LMP month is debatable (see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Prenatal_development_table.svg).

value.value: Fetal stage when the fetus is over 16 and under 17 weeks of development.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 17 and under 18 weeks of development.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 18 and under 19 weeks of development.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 19 and under 20 weeks of development.

definition.value: The cochlea has reached adult size within the fully developed inner ear (see http://ehd.org/resources_bpd_documentation_english.php). The assignation of this week to the sixth or fifth LMP month is debatable (see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Prenatal_development_table.svg).

value.value: Fetal stage when the fetus is over 20 and under 21 weeks of development.

definition.value: The lungs gain some ability to breathe air. This stage is considered the age of viability because survival outside the womb becomes possible for some fetuses (see http://ehd.org/resources_bpd_documentation_english.php).

value.value: Fetal stage when the fetus is over 21 and under 22 weeks of development.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 22 and under 23 weeks of development.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 23 and under 24 weeks of development.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 24 and under 25 weeks of development.

definition.value: The assignation of this week to the seventh or sixth LMP month is debatable (see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Prenatal_development_table.svg).

value.value: Fetal stage when the fetus is over 25 and under 26 weeks of development.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 26 and under 27 weeks of development.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 27 and under 28 weeks of development.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 28 and under 29 weeks of development.

definition.value: The assignation of this week to the eighth or seventh LMP month is debatable (see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Prenatal_development_table.svg).

value.value: Fetal stage when the fetus is over 29 and under 30 weeks of development.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 30 and under 31 weeks of development.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 31 and under 32 weeks of development.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 32 and under 33 weeks of development.

definition.value: The assignation of this week to the eighth or ninth LMP month is debatable (see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Prenatal_development_table.svg).

value.value: Fetal stage when the fetus is over 33 and under 34 weeks of development.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 34 and under 35 weeks of development.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 35 and under 36 weeks of development.
Fetal stage when the fetus is over 36 and under 37 weeks of development.

label.value: 38th week post-fertilization and over human stage

value.value: Fetal stage when the fetus is over 37 weeks of development and until birth.

definition.value: The assignation of this week to the ninth or tenth LMP month is debatable (see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Prenatal_development_table.svg).

value.value: Human developmental stage that covers the period from birth until 12 years old.
Immature stage that refers to child who is over 2 and under 13 years old.
Immature stage that refers to a newborn who is under 32 days old.
Immature stage that refers to an infant who is over 31 days and is under 24 months old.
Child stage that refers to a child who is over 24 months and under 6 years old.
Child stage that refers to a child who is over 6 and under 13 years old.
Mature stage that refers to an adolescent who is over 13 and under 19 years old.
Human developmental stage that refers to an adult who is over 19.
